The paper discusses a new local search method for constructing Bayesian network structures, which is a topic related to artificial intelligence and machine learning (cs.AI). The paper also evaluates the proposed method on several test problems, which falls under the category of machine learning and data mining (cs.LG). The concept of equivalence between network structures is also mentioned, which is related to discrete mathematics (cs.DM). The paper also discusses the efficiency of the proposed method, which is related to information theory (cs.IT). Finally, the paper discusses the use of directed acyclic graphs (DAGs), which is related to systems and control (cs.SI).
